class Solution {
public:
    void helper(int idx,vector<int>& nums,vector<int> ds,vector<vector<int>>& res)
    {
      if(idx<0)
      {
        res.push_back(ds);
        return;
      }

      //pick case
      ds.push_back(nums[idx]);
      helper(idx-1,nums,ds,res);
      //backtrack
      ds.pop_back();

      //remove duplicates 
      while(idx>0 && nums[idx]==nums[idx-1]) 
      {
        idx--;
      }

      //not pick 
      helper(idx-1,nums,ds,res);
    }
    vector<vector<int>> subsetsWithDup(vector<int>& nums) 
    {
        vector<vector<int>> res;
        sort(nums.begin(),nums.end());
        vector<int> ds;
        helper(nums.size()-1,nums,ds,res);
        return res;
    }
};

Time Complexity: O(n × 2ⁿ)

- Sorting the array takes O(n log n).
- Each element has two choices (Pick / Not Pick), generating up to 2ⁿ recursive calls.
- Copying each subset into the result takes O(n).
- Therefore, total time = O(n × 2ⁿ). (The O(n log n) sorting is dominated.)

Space Complexity:

Auxiliary Space: O(n)
- Maximum recursion depth is n.

Including Output: O(n × 2ⁿ)
- The result stores up to 2ⁿ subsets, each of size up to n.
